CINNAMON DOLCE LATTE! ☕️ You’re gonna want to save this recipe- it’s so easy and has been making my mornings SO much better. 

So when you don’t feel like heading to the coffee shop, make yourself a delicious cinnamon dolce latte at home! 

To make the syrup, you’ll need:
* 1 cup packed dark brown sugar
* 1 cup water
* 3 cinnamon sticks
* 1 tsp vanilla extract

1. Add sugar and water into saucepan and bring to a boil over medium high heat. Boil for 5 minutes to allow the flavors to caramelize a bit. 
2. Remove from heat, add cinnamon sticks, and allow them to steep for 10 minutes. 
3. Add vanilla extract and stir to mix. 
4. Let cool and store in the fridge in a sealed container for up to 10 days. 

To make the latte:
- start with hot coffee or steamed espresso 
- Add 2-3 tbsp of the cinnamon dolce syrup (totally depends on your sweetness preference)
- Add steamed milk 
- Top with the foam from the steamed milk (or whipped cream) 
- Finish with a dusting of cinnamon and ENJOY!

EASY BRUSCHETTA is a perfect appetizer for the holidays or game day- and this one is extra special, made with my hilarious single tomato 🤣

For those who have no idea what I’m talking about- I’ve been tending to this tomato plant for months and it sprouted one single tomato in DECEMBER and looked like the Charlie Brown Christmas tree. So I had to give it a proper send off and make a recipe that really shows it off. So tiny bruschetta it is! 

But really, here’s my actual bruschetta recipe for when you want to use more than one tomato:

Bruschetta
* 3 cups Roma tomato about 6 tomatoes, chopped
* 2 cloves fresh garlic pressed
* 1 tbsp olive oil
* Salt and pepper
* 3 tbsp balsamic
* 1/4 cup fresh basil
* 1 tbsp Parmesan grated

Just chop tomatoes, basil, and press garlic. Combine in a large mixing bowl with olive oil, balsamic, parmesan, salt, and pepper. Store in fridge to let it marinate for 30 min before serving. Enjoy!

Next up in my Trader Joe’s recipe series? The steak with goat cheese polenta. 🥩 It may look like something that came from a fancy restaurant, but I promise you can make this at home, it’s super easy, and so so so good.

You’ll need: 
- Steak of choice
- Balsamic vinegar
- 3-4 cloves Garlic
- Salt and pepper 
- Fresh thyme and Rosemary
- Balsamic vinegar to deglaze pan 
- One tube of polenta 
- One garlic herb goat cheese log
- Brussel sprouts or veg of choice 

Pull your steak out about an hour before you plan to cook it so it can come to room temp. Open up your steak, pat it dry, season both sides well with salt and pepper. Heat a cast-iron over medium high heat until hot, add avocado oil to the pan, and sear the steak for 2 to 3 minutes per side depending on the thickness. Cook it to your liking, and in the last two minutes of cooking, reduce heat to a simmer and add 2 tablespoons of butter, fresh herbs, and thinly sliced fresh garlic, and baste the steak continuously. Remove the steak and add 3 tbsp of balsamic vinegar and let reduce for 2 to 3 minutes until the vinegar thickens up.

Wash and chop your brussels sprouts, seasoned with salt pepper and garlic powder, spray well with cooking spray, and air fry at 375 for 13 to 14 minutes for crispy sprouts.

Cut up the polenta log and put in a microwave safe bowl, crumble cheese over top and microwave in 45 second increments, mixing as you go, until you’re able to mix it all together and have a smooth, cheesy mixture.

Put polenta down as your base, serve crispy brussels sprouts on the side, and layer steak that has been sliced against the grain over the polenta. Spoon some of the balsamic reduction with the herbs and garlic over top of the steak as a sauce and enjoy!

My new favorite meal? These LASAGNA ROLL UPS made with San Giorgio® lasagna! #ad @sangiorgio_pasta cooks perfectly every time, is made from quality ingredients (no preservatives/GMOs, thank you!), and makes for the tastiest meaty, cheesy, delicious dinner. Grab the recipe below and be sure to save this to make these yourself!

Ingredients:
-16 oz San Giorgio® Lasagna
-2 containers(16 oz.) low-fat ricotta cheese
- 2 eggs, beaten
- 1/2 cup grated Parmesan cheese
- 1 1/2 tsp salt
- 1/4 tsp ground black pepper
- 1/4 tsp garlic powder
- 2 pkgs (10 oz.) frozen chopped spinach, thawed, well drained
- 2 cups cooked, cooled crumbled sausage
- 4 cups shredded mozzarella cheese
- 2 jars(24 oz.) pasta sauce

Cooking Directions:

1.  Prepare pasta according to package directions; drain. Preheat oven to 350ºF.

2.  In a medium bowl, blend ricotta, eggs, Parmesan cheese, salt, ground black pepper, and garlic powder.

3.  Stir in spinach, sausage crumbles, and 2 cups mozzarella cheese. Spread ricotta mixture evenly on lasagna strips. Roll up each strip.

4.  In two 12 x 8-inch baking dishes, spread one-third the sauce. Place roll-ups seam-side-down in sauce.

5.  Top with remaining sauce. Sprinkle with remaining 2 cups mozzarella cheese.

6.  Cover. Bake in a 350ºF oven until hot, 45 to 50 minutes.

✨CINNAMON SCONES WITH A MAPLE GLAZE! ✨ Made with @swervesweetie, these buttermilk scones are quick and easy, making them perfect for holidays and chilly winter mornings alike. The maple glaze also takes these over the top - seriously, people will think they came from a bakery. Grab the recipe below and don’t forget to save it for later! 

Ingredients (makes 6 scones):

Scones:
* 1.5 cups all-purpose flour
* 1/4 cup Swerve Granular
* 1/2 tsp salt
* 1 1/4 tsp baking powder
* 1/4 tsp baking soda
* 6 tbsp unsalted butter, frozen and grated
* 1/2 cup + 1 tbsp buttermilk
* 1 Tsp Cinnamon 
* Brush with milk or egg and sweet cinnamon mix (2 tbsp Swerve Granular + 1/2 Tsp cinnamon) 

Glaze 
* 2 tbsp unsalted butter
* 1/2 cups Swerve Confectioners
* 2 tbsp maple syrup
* splash vanilla

Instructions
* Preheat the oven to 385 F. Grease cookie sheet or place down silicone baking mat so scones don’t stick.
* Grate frozen butter into a small bowl and put back in the freezer. 
* In a mixing bowl, combine flour, granular swerve, salt, cinnamon, baking powder and baking soda.
* Add the grated butter and gently mix with a fork until the mixture looks coarse.
* Make a well in the middle and add buttermilk. Mix until just combined. Transfer to a floured surface.
* Lightly knead the dough into a roughly 3/4 inch thick, 6-inch diameter round. Be sure not to over knead and melt the butter - you want visible chunks! Cut the round into 6 wedges and place on prepared baking pans, about 2 inches apart.
* Brush with milk and top with sweet cinnamon mixture. 
* Bake for 14-16 minutes or until lightly browned.
* Remove from the oven and serve warm.

Glaze 
* In a medium saucepan, melt butter over medium heat. Add maple syrup and vanilla, stirring to combine.
* Remove from stove top and slowly add Swerve Confectioners. Stir together until the mixture is smooth.
* Drizzle over scones immediately (glaze will begin to harden quickly)

These HEALTHY GINGERBREAD TRUFFLES are going to blow your mind. They taste like the holidays and are SO easy - plus, they’re gluten free, dairy free, and just really dang delicious. 

To make them, you’ll need:
- 1/3 cup melted chocolate of choice (if following WW, use @lilys_sweets, can also use a vegan chocolate to make these vegan, etc)
- 1/4 cup almond butter or cashew butter 
- 2 tsp molasses 
- 1/2 tsp apple pie spice (cinnamon, nutmeg, allspice)
- 1/2 tsp cinnamon 

Just melt your chocolate and put a little bit into etch truffle mold, swirling it around (I pinch the bottoms) to fully coat them. Pop in the freezer for a few min to allow to harden. Meanwhile, combine almond butter, molasses, and spices in a bowl and mix well. Fill each truffle mold with a dollop of the almond butter mixture, top with more melted chocolate to seal, and top with flaked sea salt or sprinkles to decorate. Let harden in the fridge for ~30 minutes or so and enjoy!

JALAPENO CHEDDAR PINWHEELS! These are the perfect holiday appetizer, and you’d never guess how quick and easy they are to make!! [ ad ] These pinwheels are made with real jalapenos, cheddar cheese, and @heluvagooddips Jalapeno Cheddar Dip (made with real milk and cream, never oils, so it bakes up perfectly) which takes them to the next level. Grab the recipe below and head to the link in my bio to get your dip on! #HeluvaGoodHoliday

Recipe Ingredients:
- 1 sheet puff pastry, thawed
- 1 egg
- 1 tablespoon water
- 4 ounces cream cheese, softened to room temperature
- 1/4 cup Heluva Good! Jalapeno Cheddar Dip
- 3 tbsp canned jalapeño, diced (or use fresh if you like heat)
- 1 1/2 cups sharp cheddar cheese, shredded

Instructions:
1. Preheat the oven to 400°F and line a baking sheet with parchment paper.
2. Whisk egg and water together in a small bowl, set aside.
3. Unfold pastry sheet on lightly floured surface and brush with egg wash. Set aside.
4. In a small bowl, add cream cheese, chopped jalapeño peppers, Heluva Good! Jalapeno Cheddar Dip, and cheddar cheese. Mix together until everything is fully incorporated.
5. Spread cream cheese mixture evenly over puff pastry.
6. Starting from the longer side, roll up tightly into a log shape.
7. Cut into 12 slices. Lay flat on a baking sheet. Brush tops with egg mixture.
8. Bake for 15-20 minutes or until golden brown. Serve with an extra side of dip  and enjoy!

HEALTHY COOKIE BUTTER MUDDY BUDDIES! (Or puppy chow, depending what you call this hehe)

These are SO good that I made and ate an entire batch in one day, oops!!! They’re totally #glutenfree and #vegan and made without added dairy! Grab the recipe below, don’t forget to save + share with friends! 

Ingredients:
- 2 cups rice @chexcereal 
- 6 tbsp @oat.haus original granola butter 
- 1 Tsp coconut oil 
- 1/2 cup powdered sugar 
- 1/2 Tsp cinnamon 
- 1 tbsp sprinkles (optional) 

1. Combine granola butter + coconut oil in a bowl and microwave for ~30-45 seconds, until melted and runny. Stir together.
2. Pour Chex into a large mixing bowl and coat with granola butter mixture. Gently toss to coat all of the cereal. Let cool for 5-10 minutes. 
3. Sprinkle with cinnamon and add half the powdered sugar. Toss to coat. Add sprinkles and rest of powdered sugar (use more than 1/2 cup if anything is still wet at all) and coat all of the cereal so you have little clumps. 
4. Pop in the fridge for 30 min to firm up and enjoy! Store leftovers (if there are any) in the fridge.

PB&J BANANA BITES are my latest sweet snack obsession ✨. They’re quick and easy to make, #glutenfree and #vegan and soooo yummy. They’re WW friendly and great for kids and adults alike, and I proooomise you’ll love the flavor combo. I always have these in the freezer for when I want a sweet treat (which is always). Get the details below! 

🍌🍓🥜 ingredients:
Makes 12 bites:
•1 banana cut into 24 slices 
•1.5 tbsp pb 
•2 Tsp jam of choice 
•~1/4 cup chocolate chips (if following WW about 95 lilys chips)
•1/2 Tsp coconut oil 

1. Slice banana and pipe ring of peanut butter onto 12 slices, leaving a space in the center for the jam 
2. Fill center of each peanut butter ring with jam, top with banana slice, and freeze for 20-30 minutes 
3. Melt chocolate chips with coconut oil and dip each banana bite half way into chocolate and top with flaked sea salt 
4. Freeze for 20 min so chocolate can set and enjoy! Store in the freezer. 

5 WW points per 4 bites!

Getting some warmer weather in the city today so I’m all about the fresh and easy snacks. These easy PB&J BITES are a fave of mine! They’re easy to throw together, #glutenfree #dairyfree #vegan #ww friendly, and soooo yummy. Throw some together and keep them in the freezer for a snack or dessert! 

Here’s what you’ll need (makes 16)👇🏼
-16 strawberries, sliced
-1/2 Tsp peanut butter in each (2.5 tbsp total ish)
-1/4 cup chocolate of choice melted with 1/2 Tsp coconut oil
-Flaked sea salt for topping

Directions
1. Slice strawberries and fill with 1/2 Tsp peanut butter. Freeze for 30-60 minutes.

The weather outside is chillllly which means we are still in the prime of soup season baby. This tomato gnocchi soup is like a hug in a bowl! It’s warm, comforting, tastes amazing, and it comes together super quickly and easily. It’s the latest of my Trader Joe’s recipe series, and I think you’re gonna love it!

Ingredients:
- 1 carton creamy tomato soup (32oz)
- 2 cups gnocchi 
- 3 roasted garlic chicken sausages, cut up 
- 2-3 cups baby spinach 
- Parmesan Reggiano, for garnish 
- Basil
- Salt/pepper, to taste 

Put medium saucepan over medium heat and add 1 tablespoon of olive oil. Add frozen gnocchi and toss for 1 to 2 minutes and then cover with soup. Skipped the takeout and made some Chicken Tikka Masala with Garlic Naan at home! 🤌

For the chicken- I cooked up chicken with salt and pepper and added some tikka masala simmer sauce (I used @saffronroadfood ) and simmered it for ~10 minutes until thickened. Finished it with some fresh chopped cilantro and it was delish! 

It paired perfectly with this Garlic Naan that’s #WW friendly and insanely tasty! To make it, you’ll need:

- 1 cup nonfat Greek yogurt 
- 1 cup flour 
- 1 1/2 Tsp baking powder
- 1/2 Tsp salt 
- 5 cloves of pressed garlic, minced finely 

1. Combine flour, baking powder, and salt in a bowl. Mix together. Add Greek yogurt and mix until a dough forms. Fold in half of the garlic. 
2. Flour a surface well, divide dough into 6 even pieces. On a well floured surface, roll each piece into a ball and then flatten each piece. Top with additional the rest of the fresh garlic to the tops of each piece. 
3. Heat oil over medium heat and pan fry naan until browned/bubbled (about 2 min per side). 

Makes 6 naan at 2 points each!

Enjoy!

CREAMY CRAB DIP WITH SOFT PRETZEL NUGGETS! 🤩This dip is creamy, dreamy, crabby, and delicious, and it pairs perfectly with some salty, chewy, soft @superpretzel nuggets! #partner 

Today is #NationalSoftPretzelDay and there’s no better way to celebrate than with SUPERPRETZEL - produced by Philly-local brand @jjsnackfoods! These are so quick and easy to make at home, and are perfect for dipping + snacking. 

Pair these tasty pretzels with this cool, creamy, flavor-packed dip. Grab the recipe below and don’t forget to save it for later!

Ingredients:
* 1.5 cup fresh jumbo lump crab meat (about 12 oz)
* 6 ounce light cream cheese, block kind
* 3 tbsp light Mayo 
* 3 tbsp nonfat Greek yogurt 
* 2 cloves garlic, minced
* ¼ cup chopped green onion (additional 1 tbsp of green onion for garnish) 
* 1 tbsp Worcestershire sauce
* ½ of a lemon, juiced
* Zest of 1/3 lemon 
* ½ tsp hot sauce (can add more if you like spice) 
* 2 1/2 tsp Old Bay seasoning
* Salt/ pepper to taste 
* 1 tsp onion powder 
* 1 box SUPERPRETZEL Soft Pretzel Nuggets, heated according to package directions

Directions:
1. Add cream cheese to a bowl and use a spoon to press it and loosen it up a bit. Add greek yogurt and mayo and mix together until smooth. 
2. Add garlic, green onion, old bay, onion powder, salt, pepper, worcestershire sauce, lemon juice and zest, and hot sauce. Mix well. 
3. Gently fold in crab meat (don’t over-mix - you want to leave some chunks!)
4. Garnish with extra green onions and serve with @superpretzel soft pretzel nuggets. Store leftovers in an airtight container in the fridge for up to 3 days. 

Makes 8 servings of ~1/4 cup of dip each @ 3 WW points! 

*Note: If you prefer a hot crab dip, you can add 1 cup of cheddar cheese and bake at 375 for 15-20 minutes, until bubbly and melted.

💥SWEET SRIRACHA CHICKEN BITES💥

I am a sucker for anything sweet and spicy, which is what inspired these tasty bites! These are awesome in sandwiches, over rice with some veg, or just on their own! I like to dip them in some ranch for a flavor explosion that’s high in protein, WW friendly, and just really dang delicious.

Makes 4 servings 
- 2 large chicken breasts, cut into chunks and cooked 
- 1 tbsp sriracha 
- 1 tbsp ketchup 
- 3 tbsp brown sugar substitute(I use @swervesweetie) 
- 1 tbsp rice vinegar 
- 1 tbsp coconut aminos 
- 1/2 Tsp ginger 
- 1 clove garlic 
- Cornstarch slurry - 1 Tsp corn starch mixed with 1 Tsp water 
- (Optional) 4 tbsp light ranch 

1. Cut your chicken into chunks, season with salt and pepper, spray well with cooking spray and cook until fully done using your favorite method (I air fry for 14 min at 360F). 
2. Combine all sauce ingredients except for cornstarch slurry in a small sauce pan and mix together.
3. Stir sauce over medium heat for 3 to 4 minutes, until just starting to bubble. Add cornstarch slurry and mix for about a minute, until sauce thickens. Remove from heat.
4. Toss chicken chunks in sauce and coat fully. Serve with a side of light ranch and enjoy! 

2 servings is 1 WW point! Enjoy!

PB&J YOGURT CUP WITH A CHOCOLATE SHELL 🤩

Ingredients:
-1 5.3 oz Greek yogurt (I used @fage 0%)
-2 tbsp chopped berries

-1.5 Tsp monk fruit sweetener 
-2 tbsp chocolate, melted (if following WW opt for a sugar free option like @lilys_sweets )

3. Spread melted chocolate over the top of the yogurt mixture and top with peanuts/sea salt. 
4. Freeze for 10-15 minutes, until the chocolate hardens. 
5. Crack into it and enjoy!

LOW CARB PASTA DINNER! 🍝 If you’re a volume eater like me then this recipe is for YOU! Hearts of palm pasta is a perfect alternative to regular pastas, it has a super mild flavor so it takes sauce as well, and the best part? Zero points on WW. It’s a low carb, keto, and super versatile.

I whipped up this dinner in about 20 minutes using ingredients I had at home and it was soooo yummy. I ended up pairing it with some chicken sausage for a meal that was high in protein, fiber, and of course, flavor!

Makes 2 servings at 4 WW points each. 

Ingredients:
- 8 oz package hearts of palm pasta, rinsed well 
- 4 cloves garlic, chopped 
- 1/4 cup fresh basil, chopped 
- 2 cups cherry tomatoes 
- 1.5 tbsp olive oil 
- 1 tbsp balsamic 
- 1 tbsp Parmesan cheese to top 
- (Optional) balsamic glaze drizzle 

1. Drain your hearts of palm pasta and rinse it thoroughly. Set aside.
2. Heat olive oil in a skillet over medium heat and add garlic. Sauté for two minutes, until fragrant. Add tomatoes and cook for an additional 5 to 7 minutes, until the tomatoes start to burst. Add balsamic vinegar and mix.
3. Add hearts of palm pasta and basil and sauté over medium low heat for about five minutes, until the pasta reaches your desired level of tenderness. Season with salt and pepper to taste.
4. Plate your pasta and top with fresh grated Parmesan cheese. I also like to add a little drizzle of balsamic glaze for some extra flavor, but this is totally optional. Enjoy!

🍕 5 MINUTE PIZZA! And it’s WW friendly, delicious, and totally customizable. It’s made in the air fryer (or you can use the oven), so it’s a super quick and easy no-fuss spin on pizza. Read on for the details!

- 2 tbsp pizza sauce (I used @contadina brand, or you can sub any tomato sauce)
- 1/4 cup low fat shredded mozzarella (you can use fat free for less points, but it doesn’t melt as well in my opinion)

2 INGREDIENT GUMMIES! 🙌

Two ingredients are all it takes to make tasty, squishy, chewy gummies at home. Made with your favorite fruit juice and beef gelatin which is higher in protein, Paleo, and gives great texture. These are a great way to make a lightened up version of your favorite gummy flavors! 

I used @minutemaid zero sugar mango passion fruit juice for the gummy bears and unsweetened cranberry juice for the dinos (which is sour so I had a lil sweet and sour mix). 

You’ll need:
- 1/2 cup juice of choice 
- 2 tbsp grass fed beef gelatin
- (Optional) 2-3 tbsp monk fruit sweetener if you’re using a non sweet tasting juice 

Add gelatin to juice and mix together. Put in a saucepan over medium heat and bring just to a boil, stirring well to ensure that the gelatin fully dissolves and the juice looks clear. Remove from heat, pipe into your gummy molds, and let sit in the fridge for at least 2 to 3 hours. Enjoy!

Makes about 100 small gummies, at 1 WW point for all of em if using a no sugar juice!

For the truffles:
- 1 cup of sugar free chocolate chips (or any semi sweet or dark chocolate you have)
- 1/3 cup @octonutsca Salted Caramel Cashew Butter
- Flaked sea salt, for topping 

1. Melt chocolate in microwave safe dish in 30 second intervals, stirring in between to ensure it melts fully and is smooth 
2. Put a dollop of chocolate in the base of your molds (about ½ tsp worth) and swirl it around to fully cover the outside of the mold (I pinch the bottoms to distribute the chocolate). Pop in the freezer for 2 minutes, to solidify chocolate. 
3. Fill each truffle with cashew butter (about ½-1 tsp in each). 4. Top with additional melted chocolate to cover and a dash of flaked sea salt. Put in the fridge for at least an hour to let it harden fully. Then, pop them out of the molds and enjoy!

WW points will depend on the truffle molds you use/how many you make, but mine came out to ~2 points each!

STRAWBERRY CHEESECAKE YOGURT CUP WITH A CHOCOLATE SHELL 🍓

The latest in my yogurt cup series and it is a GOODIE 🤌. High in protein, WW friendly, and has all the flavor of strawberry cheesecake (plus chocolate!). Loaded with fresh berries and crushed cookies, it’s a combo of flavors and textures that I’m sure you’ll love as much as I do! Be sure to save this post to make this later! 

Ingredients:
- 1 5.3 oz Greek yogurt 
- 2 tbsp diced berries (about 2-3 strawberries)
- 4 crushed @nillawafers 
- 1/2 Tsp vanilla extract 
- 1.5 Tsp monk fruit sweetener (I use @splenda)
- 2 tbsp chocolate, melted (if following WW opt for a sugar free option like @lilys_sweets )
- Sea salt / crushed nilla wafers for topping 

Directions:
1. Stir vanilla + monk fruit into yogurt. Add berries and crushed nilla wafersfold in. Smooth out the top. 
2. Melt chocolate in 30 sec intervals in the microwave, stir until smooth. 
3. Spread melted chocolate over the top of the yogurt mixture and top with cookie crumbs/sea salt. 
4. Freeze for 5-10 minutes, until the chocolate hardens. 
5. Crack into it and enjoy! 

Comes out to 5 WW points!

Here’s what you’ll need:
- 1 cup of nonfat Greek yogurt
- 5 raspberries, chopped
- 1/2 tsp vanilla extract
- 2 tsp monk fruit sweetener 
- 2 @nillawafers, chopped
- 40 @lilys_sweets white chocolate chips

1. Crush Nilla wafers and chop raspberries. Add monk fruit sweetener, vanilla, raspberries, and Nilla wafers to yogurt up and stir together. 
2. Smooth out the top of the yogurt so it’s flat.

4. Pour white chocolate over top of the yogurt cup and finish with some crushed Nilla wafer crumbs. Put in the freezer for 5 minutes for the chocolate to harden. 
5. Remove from freezer, crack into the shell, mix it in, and enjoy!

- 1 yellow squash, sliced into rounds then halved

1. Heat pan to medium-high heat, spray with cooking spray, and add onion and sauté for 3-4 minutes. Add chicken and sauté for another 3-4 minutes, until warmed through. Add squash and corn and toss for another 5-7 minutes, until soft. 
2. Mix ingredients for honey lemon vinaigrette in a small bowl and taste to adjust seasonings. 
3. Spoon dressing over skillet mixture and enjoy!

Ingredients (makes 2 bowls)

- 2 salmon filets, cooked (can be cold or hot)
- 2 cups diced cucumber, seeds removed 
- 1/2 avocado, diced 
- 7 seaweed snack sheets, crumbled 
- 2 tbsp light Mayo mixed with 1 Tsp sriracha 
- 4 tsp unagi sauce 
- Chili garlic crunch or sesame seeds for topping 
- Diced green onion, for garnish 

Directions:
1. Cook salmon using your preferred method (I air fry at 390F for 12-14 min, until the internal temp reaches 145F)
2. Cook rice according to package instructions and add 1/2 cup of rice to 2 bowls 
3. Add salmon filet on top of rice, then add 1 cup of cucumber and 1/2 of the diced avocado onto each bowl 
4. Mix up spicy Mayo and drizzle 1 tbsp on each bowl 
5. Drizzle 2 Tsp unagi sauce over each bowl 
6. Crumble seaweed sheets over top of the bowl and finish with some chili ginger crunch seasoning or sesame seeds. Add diced green onion and enjoy!

CHOCOLATE COVERED STRAWBERRY TURKEYS! 🍓🍫🦃

I’ve seen these allll over the Internet and had to try them! Definitely tedious but the end result was really cute. They’re a great no-bake dessert option that’s WW friendly too! 

You’ll need:
- strawberries
- 2 mini marshmallows for each berry 
- 1 mini pretzel stick per berry (broken in half)
- Melted milk or dark chocolate to dip the berries (I melted about a cup for 10-12 of these) + a tiny bit of coconut oil 
- A tiny bit of melted white chocolate to do the feet (I melted about 2 tbsp for all of these) 

1. Wash and dry your berries thoroughly. Melt chocolate by microwaving in 30 sec intervals and stirring in between. Add a tiny bit of coconut oil (1/2 Tsp per cup of chocolate) and mix in. 
2. Break pretzel stick in half, insert each piece into mini marshmallow. Dip marshmallow into melted chocolate and stick onto the sides of the berry, holding it on for a few sec so it can adhere. Put in the fridge or freezer for a few min to solidify. 
3. Once the legs are solidified on, skewer each berry with a fork or dowel, then dip in chocolate. You may need to use a spoon to help cover the berries- try to get an even coating on and then put in fridge or freezer for at least 15-30 min to let the chocolate harden. 
4. Melt white chocolate in 15 sec intervals in the microwave, stirring in between. Once melted, dab a little bit of white onto the feet of the turkeys and let harden. Enjoy!

EASY PESTO TWISTS! 🤤 The perfect no-fuss holiday appetizer or snack, these require just a handful of ingredients and are made better with @filippoberio_us olive oil + pesto. #FilippoBerioPartner The robust, rich flavors of the sun-dried tomato pesto and classic pesto pair perfectly with the flaky, buttery puff pastry, and the mild flavor or the olive oil ties it all together!

Makes 12 twists

Ingredients:
* 1 sheets puff pastry, thawed
* 3 tsp @filippoberio_us sun dried tomato pesto 
* 3 tsp @filippoberio_us basil pesto 
* 2 tbsp shredded parmesan cheese
* 2 tbsp @filippoberio_us olive oil
* Salt, pepper, Italian seasoning, to garnish

Directions:
- Preheat the oven to 400 degrees F and line a baking sheet with parchment paper. Set aside.
- Unfold your thawed pastry sheet unto parchment paper and cut the sheet into 8 even rectangles
- Spread 1 ½ tsp sun-dried tomato pesto onto 2 rectangles and basil pesto onto 2 rectangles. Sprinkle 1/2 tbsp of cheese on top of each, then cover each one with a plain piece of puff pastry.
- Use a fork to crimp down the edges, and then using a pizza cutter, cut each rectangle lengthwise into 3 even strips. 
- Twist each strip 4-5 times to create a twist shape. Brush with olive oil and top with some Italian seasoning, salt, and pepper. 
- Bake for 12-14 minutes, until golden brown. Remove from the oven and let cool. Arrange on a platter, serve them up, and enjoy!

CAULI GNOCCHI ALLA VODKA! The perfect comfort food that’s secretly lightened up but tastes amaaaazing (trust me). Ideal for chilly nights :) 

The recipe makes 4 servings, grab the details below and be sure to save this for later! 

Ingredients:
* 4 cups Trader Joe’s cauliflower gnocchi 
* 1/4 cup water, up to 1/2 cup if needed
* 1 tsp Smart Balance (or butter)
* 3 cloves Garlic, minced
* 1 Shallot, minced
* 3 tbsp Tomato paste
* 14 oz Diced tomatoes canned, drained
* 1/4 cup Vodka
* 1/3 cup Light cream cheese
* 1 tsp Basil dried or fresh
* 1/4 tsp Salt
* 1/4 tsp Black pepper
* 2 tbsp Parmesan cheese grated

* Heat a large skillet over medium-low heat. Add Smart Balance, shallots, and garlic. Sauté until shallots and garlic start to caramelize, about 3 minutes. 
* Add tomato paste and mix to form a uniform paste. Cook for about 5 minutes, moving the paste around the pan.
* Add vodka. Scrape the bottom of the pan with a wood spoon and move mixture around for 4-5 minutes to cook off the alcohol. 
* Meanwhile, cook cauli gnocchi using your desired method (I prefer to air fry it - spray well, 375F for 12-14 min. 
* Add cream cheese to tomato sauce and mix until combined.
* Add canned tomatoes (strained) and reduce heat to low. Simmer for 3 minutes, and add basil, salt, pepper to taste. Add water into tomato sauce can and add water to thin sauce as needed. Start with 1/4 cup, and add up to 1/2 cup until you reach your desired consistency. 
* Add pasta to sauce and mix to coat; top with additional basil and parmesan cheese.

- marshmallow fluff

- Truffle molds (linked in my bio- click this photo!)

Directions:
1. Melt chocolate in a microwave safe bowl in 30 sec increments in the microwave. Stir until smooth. 
2. Fill each mold roughly 1/3 of the way and swirl around so chocolate fully covers all sides (pinch the bottom to help spread it)
3. Pop into the freezer for 3-4 min to harden 
4. Add a bit of crushed graham cracker into the bottom of each truffle, then cover with about 1 Tsp of marshmallow fluff 
5. Top with additional melted chocolate to cover fully 
6. Tap on counter to release any air bubbles 
7. Put in freezer for 20 minutes to solidify or in the fridge for 2 hours 
8. Pop out and enjoy!
